        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I think partly agree with @da-woods. For Cython syntax I would allow proposed syntax:\n```cython\ncdef str[cython.Py_UCS4] s2  = \"...\"\n```\nbecause it is compact and in Cython syntax we can do whatever we want 😆 \n\nBut for **pure python** I would be more restrictive and not to allow what python does not support hence:\n1. for ` str[...]` I would **raise syntax error** or better type error\n2. I would introduce new syntax `typing.Annotated[str, Py_UCS4]`.\n\nThis will ensure 100% compatibility syntactically and semantically with python. From documentation:\n\n> Special typing form to add context-specific metadata to an annotation.[1]\n\n[1] https://docs.python.org/3/library/typing.html#typing.Annotated",
