        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> introduce new syntax `typing.Annotated[str, Py_UCS4]`\n\nTo me, it's unclear in this notation what the second type refers to, why it is there. It might rather suggest that a user wants a single character string (giving two alternative representations) than a string that unpacks into single `Py_UCS4` characters.\n\nI'd rather not implement such a feature than make users write this.\n\nI'd also rather avoid allowing a feature in Cython syntax but not in Python syntax, to avoid urging users into renaming their files (and losing tooling).",
